Kaleb Berry
CSCI 540
Assignment 4

Class: Transponder

Responsibilities:

* Pack aircraft type into transmission packets

* Pack flight data into transmission packets

* Transmit encoded packets to the ground station

Collaborators:

* Aircraft

* GroundStationReceiver

Assumptions:

* Each arriving aircraft has at least one transponder

* The transponder uses the high-density packet format

Class: Aircraft

Responsibilities:

* Collect current aircraft status data

* Provide aircraft type and flight data to the transponder

Collaborators:

* Transponder

Assumptions:

* Aircraft status data has the information the ATC system needs

* Actual flight operations aren’t needed in this ATC design




Class: GroundStationReceiver

Responsibilities:

* Receive transponder broadcasts from arriving aircraft

* Unpack aircraft type and flight data from received packets

* Forward decoded aircraft data to the database

Collaborators:

* Transponder

* AircraftDatabase

Assumptions:

* All arriving aircraft transmit the correct type of packets

* Receiving and decoding the packets are handled together


Class: AircraftDatabase

Responsibilities:

* Store aircraft records

* Update aircraft records with new flight data

* Retrieve aircraft records on request

Collaborators:

* None

Assumptions:

* Each tracked aircraft has a unique identifier

* The database is the primary source of stored aircraft information

Class: ComputerGraphicsDisplay

Responsibilities:

* Build the graphical display from stored aircraft data

* Refresh the display every 10 seconds

* Show aircraft positions and summary flight data

* Show alerts for dangerous situations

* Allow controller selection of an aircraft on screen


Collaborators:

* AircraftDatabase

* DangerDetector

* AirTrafficController

Assumptions:

* The display refresh interval is fixed at 10 seconds

* Each aircraft should be mapped to a unique aircraft record

Class: DangerDetector

Responsibilities:

* Analyze stored flight data for dangerous situations

* Detect aircraft conflicts and unsafe conditions

* Generate alerts for display to the controller

Collaborators:

* AircraftDatabase

* ComputerGraphicsDisplay


Assumptions:

* Detection rules are predefined by the ATC system

* This class only flags the risk it should not make any decisions


Class: AircraftQueryService

Responsibilities:

* Accept controller requests for aircraft details

* Retrieve selected aircraft information from the database

* Return detailed aircraft information for presentation


Collaborators:

* AirTrafficController

* AircraftDatabase

* ComputerGraphicsDisplay

Assumptions:

* Queries can’t be edited

* A selected aircraft can be uniquely matched to its database record


Class: AirTrafficController

Responsibilities:

* Monitor aircraft information on the display

* Review displayed danger alerts

* Request detailed information about a selected aircraft

* Makle decisions based on aircraft information or flagged danger

Collaborators:

* ComputerGraphicsDisplay

* AircraftQueryService

Assumptions:

* The controller interacts with the system through the display

* Any extra aircraft detail requests are initiated by the user
